 "start": "2699.872","u": "Is your sister here with you?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2701.537","u": "The sister is still in Poland. She does not have the possibility of coming yet. Probably she will come."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2706.427","u": "Why did she remain there?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2708.132","u": "She go married."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2709.336","u": "Oh."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2710.049","u": "She is still quite a young child. She is eighteen years old."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2712.636","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2713.590","u": "And she couldn&#39;t travel together with me. After us more people were supposed to arrive, but it had been upset. We were informed on."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2721.101","u": "So?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2722.035","u": "Yes. Nu, possibly she will come now."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2725.253","u": "Why were you informed on? Why can&#39;t people travel?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2728.912","u": "There are found already . . . because they don&#39;t want to let us out of Poland."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2732.952","u": "Why not?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2734.086","u": "Because they understand that Jews are still quite useful to them. Because all that is ill in Poland, all that, is being reconstructed. Jewish hands are doing the reconstruction. Without us they know they won&#39;t accomplish anything. And again there exists the Jewish Committee in Poland"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2749.051","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2749.279","u": ". . . which had been founded. It stands on guard so as not to let out a single Jew from Poland [apparently a government council on Jewish affairs]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2754.782","u": "Why? The Jewish Committee is . . . doesn&#39;t want that Jews should . . ."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2757.550","u": "I don&#39;t know what kind of ideas they have. They say that one lives entirely peacefully and well in Poland, [that] one doesn&#39;t have to go to Ereta Yisroei."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2764.025","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2764.288","u": "We didn&#39;t become legalized either, because they hindered us."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2768.780","u": "The Jewish Committee?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2769.804","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2770.377","u": "Nu?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2770.630","u": "We had to be on guard against the Jewish Committee with each and every transport that we smuggled out of Poland."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2777.000","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2778.365","u": "They stand [against] us all the time and hinder us in that work. Now we sit in Henonvilleand wait again for an Alliyah, not caring what the road will be. At the first opportunity we go on."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2793.039","u": "How did you travel from the Polish border to here? You were first in Czechoslovakia?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2797.732","u": "Yes, in Czechoslovakia. In Prague."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2798.255","u": "How long were you in Czechoslovakia?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2799.910","u": "Two weeks"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2800.804","u": "Two weeks? And then you . . . how did you travel?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2803.030","u": "To France."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2803.884","u": "By busses?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2805.269","u": "We traveled second class [good accommodations], thanks to the efforts of the Agudah [possibly by train]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2810.108","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2811.252","u": "Very fine."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2811.533","u": "Who, the entire group?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2812.878","u": "Not the entire group."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2814.303","u": "Who?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2814.535","u": "Most of the group."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2816.721","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2816.853","u": "First went the [members of the] Kibbutzim."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2818.759","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2819.472","u": "With us were also private people."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2821.946","u": "You belong to a Kibbutz?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2822.589","u": "But first . . . I am in a Kibbutz now?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2824.084","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2824.537","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2824.840","u": "And the private people were who?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2827.046","u": "Also people of the Agudah, and various one. If there comes . . . but in first place the Kibbutzim people were taken."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2835.222","u": "Hm. And you had traveled through where? Through Germany?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2838.781","u": "We traveled through Germany, too."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2840.376","u": "Did you stop . . . stayed there [word not clear]?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2842.592","u": "No. We only passed through."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2844.648","u": "What?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2845.231","u": "We only passed through."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2846.435","u": "Passed through, and then you came into France?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2848.341","u": "To France, yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2849.305","u": "And how long do you think you will have to wait?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2852.814","u": "We don&#39;t know. These are things which we don&#39;t know, how long . . . We have sent away already three transports to Eretz Yisroeil."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2858.648","u": "And did they arrive [reach their destination]?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2859.582","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2859.965","u": "Nu? [Words not clear.] And what do you do here?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2863.895","u": "Here we work. It differs. Tailoring."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2865.871","u": "[Words not clear.] And you?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2867.316","u": "I am the technical manager."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2868.679","u": "What . . . in what? In what?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2871.597","u": "In . . . in the kitchen."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2874.174","u": "In the . . . the . . . in the kitchen"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2875.739","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2876.883","u": "And the . . ."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2877.657","u": "No. Over the general order."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2879.543","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2879.675","u": "Simply that everything should be in good order."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2881.120","u": "Over the women or everybody?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2882.605","u": "Everybody."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2885.934","u": "Hm. Nu, is there anything more that you would want to tell us?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2890.776","u": "[Pause.] What I have told are not the protim. It is . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2894.085","u": "What are protim?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2894.708","u": "There are no protim, det- . . . details."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2897.133","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2897.677","u": "If one should want to relate the details, say about what one had lived through in one minute, one can sit and write a whole year. I figure that from the collected materials the world should know, and she can already form a picture [of] what had happened with us. And now the whole world should stand open for us with all . . . with all the forces with which they can help . . . help us so that we could arrive in Eretz Yisroeil. So that there we should be able to live our life fully and at least feel at home. Because no matter where it should be, we won&#39;t be able to find peace. America is not for us. Belgium is not for us. The whole world is not for us, because there . . . there we won&#39;t feel secure. We don&#39;t demand much happiness from life any more, because we had too much unhappiness. We already have given too much of our share to the world. But still, now we want a peaceful life and for once to feel what it means to be in one&#39;s home [homeland]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2956.248","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2957.319","u": "Maybe, because of that, we should be able to carry the responsibility for the generations which will come, that to them shouldn&#39;t happen any more what has happened to us."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2967.594","u": "Nu, what do you think to . . . for instance, in . . . nu, yes. And what would you want that one should do for you?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "2978.935","u": "The world should see to fight that for us should be opened the gates of Eretz Yisroeil. We demand nothing more. We still are quite capable people. The world shouldn&#39;t think that that we are crippled, backward [?]. There is yet much energy in us, because there is the will for revenge in us, which we cannot use up, because we are not able to. We have to do too much and work too much and shed too much blood, so that our Jewish consciecce and our Jewish heart should be able to carry that out. Or led the world carry that out. Let the world take revenge on those who have ruined us completely."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3022.870","u": "Do you have relatives in America?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "3024.963","u": "I have relatives in America."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3026.225","u": "Where are they?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "3027.377","u": "One is in San Francisco, [and] one is in New York."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3029.130","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "3030.212","u": "But till now I couldn&#39;t get their address, because when we arrived in Majdanek they took everything away from us. We went in naked, and we were given already their clothing so that I don&#39;t have their address. I would want very much to know their address."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3048.406","u": "Did you try to look for them through the HIAS?"},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "3051.490","u": "Through the HIAS? Not yet."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3053.483","u": "That is the best organization through which you can look for them."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "3056.407","u": "[Word not clear.]"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3057.389","u": "The HIAS knows how to look for people."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "3060.563","u": "Where is the HIAS? Here is Paris?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3062.186","u": "Oh, yes. The HIAS."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "3063.198","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3063.469","u": ". . . is in Paris. And they . . . and they search out . . . they understand from a few words . . . from a few names . . ."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "3071.476","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3071.967","u": ". . . to ask around. They ask around. They ask around, and they find out."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "3075.811","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3076.793","u": "That would be a good thing if you could find them. Nu, Mrs. Marcus, you have . . . it was a very important and interesting report that you have given me, and I thank you very much for your cooperation."},    {"who": "Hadassah Marcus", "start": "3090.745","u": "Adieu."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3091.697","u": "Adieu. This . . . [words not clear] . . . one moment [word not clear]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3095.184","u": "[In English] This concludes Spool number 129. We are concluding it at thirty minutes. Madame Hadassah Marcus, a continuation of part of the Spool number 128. Henonville, fifty kilometers from Paris. September 3rd, 1946. Recording of the Illinois Institute of Technology. [After a stretch of silence there follows a fragment of a song by an unidentified male voice.]"}        ]
